    <field name="scopecontent_teim">This series includes material from Scoppetta's positions as Commissioner of Investigation for the City of New York (1972–1977) and Deputy Mayor for Criminal Justice (1976–1978). There is significant coverage of NYPD Detective Robert Leuci's cooperation with the Knapp Commission's investigation of police corruption. The series also contains course readings for the seminar Scoppetta taught for New York University School of Law—"The Administration of Criminal Justice"—between 1979 and 1982. A small amount of printed matter, much of it on police corruption, rounds out the series.</field>
